</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACE5C4C3FFC7FFA8AD3DBD50FDD6FD67" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8AD3DBD50FDD6FD67" blockId="7.[111,648,575,757]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">
ETYMOLOGY. — The name alludes to the similarities with members of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AC07BD35FE52FDE3" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1929" box="[331,458,602,625]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Vepricardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AC07BD35FE52FDE3" box="[331,458,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Vepricardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in many gross shell features, more so than any other 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8ACE7BD1BFE7FFD19" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1853" box="[427,487,628,651]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8ACE7BD1BFE7FFD19" box="[427,487,628,651]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Fulvia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
studied thus far. The existence of this new intermediate form, which shares four significant characters with 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8ACDDBDC6FD93FD52" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1929" box="[401,523,681,704]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Vepricardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8ACDDBDC6FD93FD52" box="[401,523,681,704]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Vepricardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, provides the first evidence that these genera may be more closely related than previously thought (
<bibRefCitation id="806EEAB9FFC7FFA8AC29BDB1FD9BFD67" author="SCHNEIDER J. A." box="[357,515,734,757]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" pagination="145 - 155" refId="ref18081" refString="SCHNEIDER J. A. 1992. - Preliminary cladistic analysis of the bivalve family Cardiidae. American Malacological Bulletin 9 (2): 145 - 155." type="journal article" year="1992">Schneider 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="806EEAB9FFC7FFA8AF41BDB1FDDBFD67" author="SCHNEIDER J. A." box="[525,579,734,757]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" pagination="321 - 346" refId="ref18110" refString="SCHNEIDER J. A. 1995. - Phylogeny of the Cardiidae (Mollusca Bivalvia): Protocardiinae, Laevicardiinae, Lahilliinae, Tulongocardiinae subfam. n. and Pleuriocardiinae subfam. n. Zoologica Scripta 24 (4): 321 - 346." type="journal article" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACE5C4C3FFC7FFA8AD3DBC62FE52FCB7" box="[113,458,781,805]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8AD3DBC62FE52FCB7" blockId="7.[113,458,781,805]" box="[113,458,781,805]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">
DISTRIBUTION. — 
<collectingCountry id="9CE8D7D8FFC7FFA8AC67BC61FE5EFCB7" box="[299,454,782,805]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACE5C4C3FFC7FFA8AD3DBC3DFB34FD1C" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" type="description">
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8AD3DBC3DFE9AFCF8" blockId="7.[111,648,850,1700]" box="[113,258,850,876]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8AD3DBC1DFD1EFC39" blockId="7.[111,648,850,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Shell small, subcircular and subsymmetrical, very slightly oblique, and not posteriorly straightened.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8ADC4BCDEFD9CFB98" blockId="7.[111,648,850,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Lunular area small, slightly flattened, margin convex in left valve, concave in right valve; lunular heart long and narrow; no sublunule.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8ADC4BB7FFDECFB7A" blockId="7.[111,648,850,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Exterior whitish with rare, irregular, concentric pink blotching; last five posterior ribs light pink; umbo dark pink, with pink colour extending ventrally as a ray. Lunular area white. Interior white, except for a slight pink colour in the umbonal cavity and a strongly pink-stained posterodorsal margin. Adductor scars with pink spotting and staining.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8ADC4BB81FEB9FA34" blockId="7.[111,648,850,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">
Hinge plate characteristic of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AF0EBB81FEB0FABA" authority="(Vidal 1994: 97)" baseAuthorityName="Vidal" baseAuthorityPageNumber="97" baseAuthorityYear="1994" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AF0EBB81FD1FFA9A" box="[578,647,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Fulvia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="806EEAB9FFC7FFA8AD35BA61FEB8FABA" author="VIDAL J." box="[121,288,1294,1320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" pagination="93 - 118" refId="ref18357" refString="VIDAL J. 1994. - A review of the genus Fulvia Gray, 1853 (Mollusca, Bivalvia). Apex 9 (4): 93 - 118." type="journal article" year="1994">Vidal 1994: 97</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in being narrow, thin and moderately curved (120-150°), occasionally angled in the anterior. However, the hinge differs slightly from other 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8ADA3BA02FEAAFA15" baseAuthorityName="Vidal" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[239,306,1389,1415]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8ADA3BA02FEAAFA15" box="[239,306,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Fulvia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being symmetrical and with a long ligament.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8ADC4BAC3FE90FA54" blockId="7.[111,648,850,1700]" box="[136,264,1452,1478]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Ribs 52-54.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8ADC4BAA3FB34FD1C" blockId="7.[111,648,850,1700]" lastBlockId="7.[677,1210,502,654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">
Ribs (
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AD86BAA3FF43FA74" box="[202,219,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">c.</emphasis>
14) are larger in the posterior third of the shell than in the medio-anterior shell regions, and the periostracal line bears tubercles. The last five ribs in the posterior are split into two parts by a slight furrow and bear more numerous, regularly disposed, tubercles than ribs in the anterior area of the shell. On the most median and anterior part of the shell, the ribs are low, flatly rounded, slightly asymmetrical, with their posterior margin slightly raised and bearing thin periostracal insertions; interstices narrow. The anterior most ribs are flatter and larger compared with adjacent anterior ribs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACE5C4C3FFC7FFA8AFE9BDDBFBCDFB7A" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8AFE9BDDBFC91FD5E" blockId="7.[674,1210,692,1256]" box="[677,777,692,718]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4409748FFC7FFA8AFE9BDBCFBCDFB7A" blockId="7.[674,1210,692,1256]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">
As the name suggests, 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AEC8BDBBFB99FD7C" authority="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale, 2007" authorityName="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale" authorityYear="2007" box="[900,1025,724,750]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vepris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AEC8BDBBFB99FD7C" box="[900,1025,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Fulvia vepris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDB8F621FFC7FFA8A94ABDBCFBA5FD7F" box="[1030,1085,723,749]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares some characters with species in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AEB4BD9CFBE0FC9F" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1929" box="[1016,1144,755,781]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Vepricardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AEB4BD9CFBE0FC9F" box="[1016,1144,755,781]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Vepricardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: solidity of the shell, absence of a sublunular area, relatively high ribs on the median shell region and presence of carbonaceous tubercles. However, like species of 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AFE9BC1DFD7EFC1E" baseAuthorityName="Vidal" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[677,742,882,908]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AFE9BC1DFD7EFC1E" box="[677,742,882,908]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Fulvia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AFBEBC1DFCDFFC1E" authority="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale, 2007" authorityName="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale" authorityYear="2007" box="[754,839,882,908]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vepris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AFBEBC1DFC99FC1E" box="[754,769,882,908]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">F</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AE42BC1DFCDFFC1E" box="[782,839,882,908]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">vepris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDB8F621FFC7FFA8AE01BC1DFC1EFC1E" box="[845,902,882,908]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
exhibits localized periostracal insertions, possesses a well-developed lunular heart and has a typical 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AE1BBCDEFC00FC59" baseAuthorityName="Vidal" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[855,920,945,971]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AE1BBCDEFC00FC59" box="[855,920,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Fulvia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hinge. The tubercles on the anterior and posterior zones are unique to 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8A92BBCBEFB21FC79" authority="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale, 2007" authorityName="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale" authorityYear="2007" box="[1127,1209,977,1003]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vepris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8A92BBCBEFB21FC79" box="[1127,1209,977,1003]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">F. vepris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDB8F621FFC7FFA8AFE9BC9FFD46FB98" box="[677,734,1008,1034]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and immediately distinguish it from all other members of the genus. 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AEEFBB7FFBBFFBB8" authority="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale, 2007" authorityName="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale" authorityYear="2007" box="[931,1063,1040,1066]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vepris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AEEFBB7FFBBFFBB8" box="[931,1063,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Fulvia vepris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDB8F621FFC7FFA8A963BB7FFBF3FBB8" box="[1071,1131,1040,1066]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be further differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AEF1BB5FFBBAFBD8" authority="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale, 2007" authorityName="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale" authorityYear="2007" box="[957,1058,1072,1098]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="colorata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AEF1BB5FFBBAFBD8" box="[957,1058,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">F. colorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDB8F621FFC7FFA8A964BB5FFBF8FBD8" box="[1064,1120,1072,1098]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in being more solid, less elongate (L/H 1.03 compared with 0.89 for 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AFB2BB00FCFBFB1B" authority="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale, 2007" authorityName="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale" authorityYear="2007" box="[766,867,1135,1161]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="colorata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AFB2BB00FCFBFB1B" box="[766,867,1135,1161]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">F. colorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDB8F621FFC7FFA8AE25BB00FC3BFB1B" box="[873,931,1135,1161]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<tableCitation id="A97DA2F3FFC7FFA8AEE0BB00FC61FB1B" box="[940,1017,1135,1161]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="20.[113,124,219,236]" captionText="TABLE 9. — Comparison of diagnostic characters for similar Fulvia (Fulvia), F. (Laevifulvia) and Pseudofulvia n. gen. taxa occurring sympatrically in the tropical west Pacific." pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Table 9</tableCitation>
) and less intensely coloured. 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFC7FFA8AE40BBE0FC14FB3B" authority="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale, 2007" authorityName="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale" authorityYear="2007" box="[780,908,1167,1193]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Fulvia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vepris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFC7FFA8AE40BBE0FC14FB3B" box="[780,908,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Fulvia vepris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDB8F621FFC7FFA8AEDDBBE0FC53FB3B" box="[913,971,1167,1193]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is represented by a sole lot of three shells from the Dautzenberg collection (
<collectingCountry id="9CE8D7D8FFC7FFA8AFE0BBA1FCCBFB7A" box="[684,851,1230,1256]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
) housed at the MNHN.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
